Record: A pleasant trip on the Mersey Ferry RSPB Birdwatching trip today but as you would expect in this still weather sea-watching was quiet with the only highlight 1 Mediterranean Gull among all the usual gulls and Cormorants - but remarkably there were 5 Spoonbill feeding on the tide edge on Crosby Beach also on a sand bank on the Burbo Bank side of the channel were 54 Pink-footed Geese probably resting after their long journey from Iceland also c300 Pink-footed Geese on the beach just north of the Alt Estuary along with a good selection of waders
